Following attacks on villages in Zamfara State, about 6,000 displaced persons have abandoned their homes to take refuge in four  primary schools at Maradun Local Government Area of the state. About 12,000 persons had earlier been displaced from 18 communities in three districts at Zurmi Local Government Area of the state. Our correspondent, who visited a primary school in Gidan Kano village yesterday, saw women, children and elders occupying all the classrooms. The councilor representing the Birnin Kaya  /Dosara attacked by bandits, Kabiru Muhammad Danbaza, put the number of the displaced persons in his ward at 5,645. The speaker of the state House of Assembly, who is also the chairman of Damage Assessment and Relief Committee Sanusi Garba Rikiji, said 1,000 bags of assorted grains and 2,000 pieces of clothing material were distributed to the displaced persons.